  <h2>Disabled state</h2>
  <p>Make buttons look unclickable by fading them back 50%.</p>

  <h3>Anchor element</h3>
  <p>Add the <code>.disabled</code> class to <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> buttons.</p>
  <p class="bs-docs-example">
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-large btn-primary disabled">Primary link</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-large disabled">Link</a>
  </p>
<div class="tab-content">
<pre class="prettyprint linenums tab-pane fade in active" id="button-disabled-haml">
%a.btn.btn-large.btn-primary.disabled{:href => "#"} Primary link
%a.btn.btn-large.disabled{:href => "#"} Link
</pre>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums tab-pane fade" id="button-disabled-html">
&lt;a href="#" class="btn btn-large btn-primary disabled"&gt;Primary link&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href="#" class="btn btn-large disabled"&gt;Link&lt;/a&gt;
</pre>
</div>
  <ul class="nav nav-pills example-types">
    <li class="active"><a href="#button-disabled-haml" data-toggle="tab">HAML</a></li>
    <li><a href="#button-disabled-html" data-toggle="tab">HTML</a></li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    <span class="label label-info">Heads up!</span>
    We use <code>.disabled</code> as a utility class here, similar to the common <code>.active</code> class, so no prefix is required. Also, this class is only for aesthetic; you must use custom JavaScript to disable links here.
  </p>

  <h3>Button element</h3>
  <p>Add the <code>disabled</code> attribute to <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> buttons.</p>
  <p class="bs-docs-example">
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-large btn-primary disabled" disabled="disabled">Primary button</button>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-large" disabled>Button</button>
  </p>
<div class="tab-content">
<pre class="prettyprint linenums tab-pane fade in active" id="button-element-disabled-haml">
%button.btn.btn-large.btn-primary.disabled{:disabled => "disabled", :type => "button"} Primary button
%button.btn.btn-large{:disabled => "", :type => "button"} Button
</pre>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums tab-pane fade" id="button-element-disabled-html">
&lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-large btn-primary disabled" disabled="disabled"&gt;Primary button&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-large" disabled&gt;Button&lt;/button&gt;
</pre>
</div>
